  "prompt": "How do I give my girlfriend space / stop the feeling of having my soul sucked out for the seconds I'm not with her?",
  "response": "Here are some healthy ways to manage these intense feelings:\n\n1. Personal Development\n- Pursue your own hobbies and interests\n- Set personal goals\n- Exercise and maintain physical health\n- Spend time with friends and family\n\n2. Emotional Management\n- Practice mindfulness and meditation\n- Recognize that constant connection isn't healthy\n- Work on personal self-confidence\n- Understand that independence strengthens relationships\n\n3. Relationship Boundaries\n- Discuss healthy communication expectations\n- Establish mutual trust\n- Agree on reasonable check-in frequencies\n- Respect each other's individual space\n\n4. Psychological Strategies\n- Challenge clingy thoughts\n- Remember you're a complete person with or without her\n- Address potential underlying anxiety or attachment issues\n- Consider talking to a counselor if feelings feel overwhelming\n\n5. Practical Steps\n- Create a structured schedule for interactions\n- Engage in separate activities\n- Limit constant texting/calling\n- Build a balanced life outside the relationship\n\nKey principle: A healthy relationship involves two independent individuals who choose to be together, not two people who can't function separately.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
